{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WoWRJkSxWVnaMFNVVEqPui","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→\n     8→@Entity\n     9→@Inheritance(strategy = InheritanceType.SINGLE_TABLE)\n    10→@DiscriminatorColumn(name = \"LEAGUE_TYPE\")\n    11→public abstract class League implements Serializable {\n    12→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    13→\n    14→    @Id\n    15→    protected String id;\n    16→    protected String name;\n    17→    protected String sport;\n    18→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"league\")\n    19→    protected Collection<Team> teams = new ArrayList<>();\n    20→\n    21→    public League() {\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public League(String id, String name, String sport) {\n    25→        this.id = id;\n    26→        this.name = name;\n    27→        this.sport = sport;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public String getId() {\n    31→        return id;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public void setId(String id) {\n    35→        this.id = id;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    public String getName() {\n    39→        return name;\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    public void setName(String name) {\n    43→        this.name = name;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public String getSport() {\n    47→        return sport;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    public void setSport(String sport) {\n    51→        this.sport = sport;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public Collection<Team> getTeams() {\n    55→        return teams;\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public void setTeams(Collection<Team> teams) {\n    59→        this.teams = teams;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public void addTeam(Team team) {\n    63→        this.teams.add(team);\n    64→    }\n    65→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019PKKdt3gpX2i3qQEroy2Wv","session_id":"b980a48c-449a-4184-94ce-e355b0c87aac","uuid":"0029823a-f6f6-47af-bf87-90696eb06de7"}
