{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012fcr34EeofwPbnNf62w5mQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There are a few issues to fix:\n\n1. **League/Team/Player creation returns non-200 status** - The `createLeague`, `createTeamInLeague`, and `createPlayer` methods return `void`, but Spring MVC returns 200 by default for void methods. The issue is that some of the POST calls fail because `import.sql` has already pre-loaded data and there's a conflict. Wait - looking more carefully, the `import.sql` file might be loading data. Also, those methods return `void` and Spring returns 200 for void. The real issue is that the status code for these 200-returning void endpoints is interpreted wrong. Let me check what status code is actually returned.\n\n2. **The salary range endpoint has an issue** - The URL has query params appended incorrectly when they're part of the path in `request()`. \n\nLet me fix the issues. First, the void methods - in Spring, a void return type on a `@RestController` method doesn't write a response body and returns 200. But a `void` method might return 200 with an empty body. The test checks `status == 200` which should be fine for void.\n\nLet me look more carefully at the errors. The POST create methods are failing. The `import.sql` probably already has data inserted. Let me check:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1489,"cache_read_input_tokens":107403,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1489,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":403},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b980a48c-449a-4184-94ce-e355b0c87aac","uuid":"89ec1670-2a2e-4a55-a4a3-6ef0688480fd"}
