{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014UKfZfj496fKKjvTDykKih","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The HTTP error handling looks correct. The issue was actually that the traceback showed a `urllib.error.HTTPError` exception, but the except clause catches `HTTPError`. Wait - looking at the traceback, the exception wasn't caught because it happened at a different place. Let me look more carefully at the traceback:\n\n```\nFile \"/usr/lib/python3.12/urllib/request.py\", line 215, in urlopen\n    return opener.open(url, data, timeout)\n```\n\nThe error occurs inside `urlopen`. But the `except urllib.error.HTTPError` should catch it. Unless... it's a `urllib.error.URLError` (connection error, not HTTP error). The container likely had a connection issue at that point (the earlier run crashed the container).\n\nThe smoke test code is fine. Let me now just add a general exception handler and re-run:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1000,"cache_read_input_tokens":118916,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1000,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":328},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b980a48c-449a-4184-94ce-e355b0c87aac","uuid":"552d93cf-14d2-40cf-a803-7df656ea6fff"}
